message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Spain in the past 20 years is the 2004 Madrid train bombings, also known as the 11-M bombings. On March 11, 2004, a series of coordinated terrorist attacks took place in Madrid, targeting commuter trains during rush hour. The bombings resulted in the death of 191 people and injured thousands. This event had a profound impact on Spain, leading to changes in security measures, political landscape, and public opinion regarding terrorism and international relations.
